FBIS4-47800 "drafr086_d_94011" FBIS-AFR-94-086 Daily Report 3 May 1994 SOUTHERN AFRICA Zambia Chiluba Congratulates ANC Leader on Election Victory Chiluba Congratulates ANC Leader on Election Victory MB0305194594 Lusaka Zambia National Broadcasting Corporation Network in English 1800 GMT 3 May 94 MB0305194594 Lusaka Zambia National Broadcasting Corporation Network English BFN [Text] President Chiluba has sent a message of congratulations to Mandela on his victory in the just ended all-race elections. In a congratulatory message issued to ZNBC [Zambia National Broadcasting Corporation] news this evening, Mr. Chiluba said it was Zambia's prayer that Mr. Mandela gets God's blessings to attend national reconciliation. The message sent on behalf of the president by Vice President Levy Mwanawasa, described the African National Congress victory to end the apartheid regime as the world- led victory. In a similar message to outgoing President F.W. de Klerk, Mr. Chiluba lauded the last white leader of the apartheid country for handling the transition to democratic elections properly.
